bird with strings featuring andrew speight events at stanford bird with strings featuring andrew speight facebook twitter email print add to calendar recorded from 1949 through 1952 and produced by norman granz the astonishingly beautiful charlie parker with strings releases were a departure from his usual bebop quintet setting but he had good reason for choosing the format not only were these sides his biggest sellers they set the mold for a new genre of jazz with strings records including those by nat king cole clifford brown and stan getz parker didn t so much reign in his improvisatory flights of fancy on these recordings as focus on the beauty of the melodies his canny choice of contemporary pop hits such as april in paris laura and just friends ensured fertile ground for melodic expression as well as a connection to a wider audience sjw's andrew speight takes on the alto sax role with live strings playing the original arrangements from the sessions mixed with some classic parker originals the all music guide says of the original recordings that they re the perfect antidote to a surfeit of jazz records featuring undisciplined blowing inside jazz pre concert talk remembering bird saturday july 16 7 pm featuring sonny buxton kcsm jazz 91.1 when saturday july 16 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where dinkelspiel auditorium 471 lagunita dr stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $32 premium $28 general $18 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27961 more info last modified july 11 2011
